# Story 2.3: Display Depot Capacity Cards

## Story Metadata
- **Epic:** 2 - Dashboard & KPIs
- **Status:** done
- **Implemented:** 2025-12-28
- **Session:** SESSION-004

## User Story
As **Gabriel (Fleet Manager)**,
I want **depot capacity cards on the dashboard**,
So that **I can monitor maintenance capacity across depots**.

## Acceptance Criteria

| AC | Criteria | Status |
|----|----------|--------|
| AC1 | Cards show depot name and code | PASS |
| AC2 | Track capacity utilization displayed | PASS |
| AC3 | Man-hour capacity utilization displayed | PASS |
| AC4 | Visual indicator for high utilization | PASS |

## Implementation Details

### Files Created
- `apps/web/src/components/dashboard/DepotCapacityCards.tsx` - Depot cards grid

### UI Design
- Card grid with depot info
- Progress bars for capacity utilization
- Color coding: green (<70%), yellow (70-90%), red (>90%)
- Responsive: 3 columns desktop, 2 tablet, 1 mobile

### API Integration
- Fetches from `GET /api/fleet/depots`
- Calculates utilization from scheduled maintenance

## Dev Notes
Depot cards provide strategic view of maintenance capacity.
High utilization depots highlighted for attention.

